g.title: Sheet.978
g.desc: The flow represents the Token Revocation flow & Cache invalid...
g.text: The flow represents the Token Revocation flow & Cache invalidation in the WSO2 API Manager v3.2.0 server with Keycloak as Key Manager. The flow starts from receiving a Token Revocation request at the Keycloak server with the custom built Resource Provider implementation. The Revoked tokens (JTI) are stored in a cache in the Gateway servers to verify the tokens validity and to not to authorize them.
